# 📌 Feature Spec: WebUI Endpoint Inventory and Scope Extension

## 1. Feature Overview

This feature defines the endpoint contract inventory required by the Film-Review WebUI in:
- `dalogin-quarkus/src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/film-review`

It standardizes:
- which routes/controllers depend on which backend endpoints,
- which service owns each endpoint,
- what endpoint gaps block template extension beyond booking flow.

---

## 2. Scope

## ✅ Included

- Active Film-Review Angular routes currently used in `app.js`
- Endpoint mapping for `dalogin-quarkus`, `mbooks-quarkus`, `mbook-quarkus`, `simple-service-webapp-quarkus`
- Gap analysis for template pages not currently wired
- Phased extension definition (P1/P2/P3)

## 🚫 Excluded

- Rewriting AngularJS architecture
- Implementing all new endpoints in this feature
- Enabling community/profile modules before endpoint contracts exist

---

## 3. Functional Requirements

### REQ-WEI-1 Endpoint matrix

A matrix MUST be produced for each active route with these fields:
- route
- Angular controller
- HTTP method
- endpoint path
- backend service owner
- auth expectation (public/session/HMAC)
- status (`implemented` | `missing` | `partial`)

### REQ-WEI-2 Current flow coverage

The matrix MUST include all active booking-flow routes:
- `/login`
- `/change-password`
- `/movies`
- `/venues-list`
- `/venue-movies/:locationId`
- `/venues/:movieId`
- `/dates/:locationId/:movieId`
- `/checkout`
- `/purchases`
- `/purchases/:purchaseId`

### REQ-WEI-3 Service ownership validation

Each mapped endpoint MUST have one owning service:
- `dalogin-quarkus`
- `mbooks-quarkus`
- `mbook-quarkus`
- `simple-service-webapp-quarkus`

### REQ-WEI-4 Gap classification

Missing or partial endpoints MUST be categorized:
- P1: booking-complete hardening (must-have now)
- P2: discovery enhancements (trending, detail enrichment, server-side filtering)
- P3: optional community/profile modules

### REQ-WEI-5 P2 discovery contracts

The spec MUST include concrete candidate contracts for discovery extension:
- `GET /mbooks-1/rest/book/trending-movies`
- `GET /mbooks-1/rest/book/movies/{movieId}`
- `GET /mbooks-1/rest/book/movies/paging?...`
- `GET /mbooks-1/rest/book/movies/search?...`

### REQ-WEI-6 Scope guard for template modules

Template pages not in booking scope (blog/news/celebrity/profile/rating) MUST remain disabled from active nav until their endpoint contracts are marked `implemented`.

### REQ-WEI-7 Source of truth

Endpoint mapping decisions MUST be derived from code first:
- WebUI calls in `film-review/app.js`
- backend controllers in Quarkus services

README docs are supportive references, not primary authority when mismatch exists.

---

## 4. Non-Functional Requirements

### REQ-WEI-NF-1 Traceability

Each matrix row MUST be traceable to at least one concrete callsite in `film-review/app.js`.

### REQ-WEI-NF-2 Change safety

No route should be enabled in UI without a mapped endpoint owner and auth expectation.

### REQ-WEI-NF-3 Maintainability

The endpoint inventory format should remain stable so future template pages can be added without restructuring docs.

---

## 5. Deliverables

- Endpoint matrix document (route -> controller -> endpoint -> owner)
- Gap list by phase (P1/P2/P3)
- Candidate endpoint contracts for P2/P3 expansion
- Acceptance checklist for safe route enablement

---

## 6. Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] All active Film-Review routes are represented in endpoint matrix.
- [ ] Every mapped endpoint has exactly one owning backend service.
- [ ] Missing/partial endpoints are phased as P1/P2/P3.
- [ ] `trending-movies` is explicitly defined in P2 discovery scope.
- [ ] Non-booking modules are marked disabled until contract + owner exist.
- [ ] Matrix rows can be traced to `app.js` callsites.

